{{Quote|It's not a name that would ring a bell with the average Star Wars fan, but for my money Michael Allen Horne is one of the best writers of the SW Expanded Universe.|Dan Wallace|<ref name="Dan's blog">{{Blogspot|subdomain=geekosity|url=2007/08/underappreciated-star-wars-writers.html|name=Daniel Wallace's Geekosity|text=Underappreciated Star Wars Writers: Michael Allen Horne|date=2007-08-30}}</ref>}}
'''Michael Allen Horne''' (1963? - Jan 18,{{fact}} 2015) was an author who wrote material for ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' for [[West End Games]].

Horne's work on the ''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'' and ''[[Han Solo and the Corporate Sector Sourcebook]]'' has been praised by other [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] authors like [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Abel G. Peña]],<ref name="Dan's blog" /><ref name="Abel's JCF post">{{JCFCite|url=threads/thank-you.21957621/page-3#post-21991525|board=Literature|thread=Thank You|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|PTtime=2005-10-19|accessdate=2026-01-02|archivedate=20260102034722}}</ref> with Wallace calling them the "blue-ribbon standards" of gaming sourcebooks and lauding their amount of detail, color, and universe expansion.<ref name="Dan's blog" /> When Horne passed away in [[2015]], Wallace called him "one of the best writers of [[West End Games]] and the #StarWars Expanded Universe."<ref name="Wallace's Tweet">{{Twitter|username=danwallaceMSP|url=status/557578667816009728|name=[[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]|date=2015-01-24|quote=Saddened to hear of the death of Michael Allen Horne, one of the best writers of West End Games and the #StarWars Expanded Universe.|archiveurl=https://archive.md/Y3z9R#selection-507.54-517.19}}</ref>

